Mockito:

Annotations:
@Mock: Creates a mock implementation for the specified class.
@Mock : This annotation tells Mockito to create a mock instance of the CalculatorService interface.
@InjectMocks: Creates an instance of the class and injects the mocks that are marked with the @Mock annotation into it.
@InjectMocks : This annotation tells Mockito to inject the mock instances.
@Before: Annotates a method that is run before each test. In this case, it initializes the mocks.
MockitoAnnotations.openMocks(this): This line initializes the mock objects and processes the @Mock and @InjectMocks annotations.
Mocking and Stubbing:
when(calculatorService.add(10, 20)).thenReturn(30): 
Defines the behavior of the mock object. 
When the add method is called with arguments 10 and 20, it returns 30.
verify(calculatorService).add(10, 20): 
Verifies that the add method was called with arguments 10 and 20.




